On my latest podcast, I sat down with @DrWarrenFarrell, Ph.D.⁣
⁣
We discussed “The Boy Crisis”, parenting, the importance of parental dialogue and couples communication, delayed gratification, what is needed for children to do their best, the father’s catch-22, the disposable male crisis, and more.⁣
⁣
This episode is now live on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify.

Click the link in my bio for more.
⁣
Recorded 05/25/2021.

"If you take measures of parasite stress across the world, and look for the predictive relationship between parasite stress and conservatism and liberalism, and found what we expected, and strongly so: the more parasites, the more conservative. Said differently: the more parasites, the more collectivists."⁣
⁣
On my recent podcast (S4: E38) with Dr. Randy Thornhill, he shared his findings on parasite-stress theory and the critical role that infectious disease plays in humanity, IQ, sex, religion, and conservatism.⁣
⁣
Watch more of this podcast via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/11/2021.

⁣

⁣
My guests are John Vallis, Gigi Der, Robert Breedlove, and Richard James.⁣
⁣
Watch this podcast (S4: E40) on YouTube via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/13/2021.

Click the link in my bio for more.
⁣
Recorded 05/25/2021.

⁣
Recorded 03/03/2021 with @aubreymarcus

⁣
From my appearance on the "The Tim Ferris Show" - @TimFerriss⁣
⁣
Watch more on YouTube.

North Koreans have no idea what is happening in the outside world.⁣
⁣
"We do not even have electricity... In school, I never even seen a map of the world... They cut out entire information, and people literally get executed for watching foreign information."⁣
⁣
@Yeonmi_Park shared her experience escaping North Korea on my podcast (S4: E26). It's available on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, and YouTube.⁣
⁣
Recorded 04/14/2021.
